<div class="grid">
    <div class="col-1-1">
        <div class="module">
            <h1 class="center">Consent</h1>
            
        </div>
    </div>
    <div class="col-1-1">
        <div class="module">
            <h3>Identify yourself to the patient by saying "I am a first Responder"</h3>
            <h3>Then ask "May I help you?"</h3>
            <form action="/consent" method="POST">
                <div>
                    <label for="consent">Did the patient/guardian give consent? (Includes implied consent if patient is unconcious)</label><br>
                    <input type="radio" name="consent" value="y" class="radio">Yes<br>
                    <input type="radio" name="consent" value="n" class="radio">No
                </div>
                <br>
                <div>
                    <button type="submit" class="centerButton">Continue</button>
                </div>
            </form>
            <br>
            <p><strong>Important:</strong> The patient/guardian can rescend their consent at anytime. Continue to ask for consent through out the process.</p>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>